AGI - The 23-year-old convictions against anarchist Alfredo Cospito and 17 years and 9 months against Anna Beniamino are definitive. The Sixth Criminal Section of the Court of Cassation rejected the appeal lodged by the General Prosecutor of the Court of Appeal of Turin and, at the same time, declared inadmissible the appeals of the defences > : in fact, the judgment issued by the judges of the second rank of Turin, in front of which the public accused had instead requested the life sentence for Cospito. The judiciary is related to the attack on the former barracks of the Carabinieri of Fossano, in the province of Cuneo, occurred in 2006.
&nbsp;
"The determinations of the Turin appeal court appear correct," said the Deputy Attorney General of the Cassation, Perla Lori, during his requisite: "the damage actually achieved" - the magistrate has asserted - "has been mild." After the general prosecutor, the defenders of Alfredo Cospito and Anna Beniamino, the lawyers Flavio Rossi Albertini and Caterina Calia. In the morning of today, in front of the Palazzo della Cassazione, some anarchists had created a sit-in, during which banners were exhibited as "out of Alfredo from 41bis" and "the prison kills". &nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;
